File Path in HTML :

A file path tells the browser where a file (image, CSS file, JavaScript file, video, etc.) is located.

Example: <img src="image.jpg" alt="Image"> Here image.jpg is the file path.
 <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> The browser looks for style.css and applies the styles.

Types of File Paths:
1.Relative File Path: A relative path specifies the location relative to the current HTML file.
  Example Structure:
project/
